A command-line tool for generating Julia set fractals.

Usage
=====

```bash
python run.py <density-pixel> <detail-density> <cr> <ci> [options]
```

Required Arguments
==================
- `density-pixel`: Resolution of the output image
- `detail-density`: Level of detail in the fractal
- `cr`: Real part of complex parameter c
- `ci`: Imaginary part of complex parameter c

Optional Arguments
==================
- `-c, --color THEME`: Color theme for the fractal
- `-s, --save FILENAME`: Save the output to an image file

Example
=======
```bash
python run.py 500 300 -0.4 0.6 -c "inferno" -s "output.jpg"
```

Use `--help` for detailed information about all available options.
